definition: to arrive at (place or time)/period/to become due/classifier for events, meetings, elections, sporting fixtures, years (of graduation)
person representing the dead (during burial ceremonies)/to put a corpse on display (after execution)/variant of 屍|尸[shi1]/corpse
when the time comes/at the scheduled time
the end of fixed period in office/expiration of a term
to extend all over the globe (idiom)/far-reaching
student graduating in the current year/recent graduate

sentences.english: Entry form will be destroyed before the commencement of next Music Festival.
sentences.chinese: 報名表將於來屆音樂節開始前銷燬。

sentences.english: What is the largest construction project of the 16th Asian Games?
sentences.chinese: 第16屆亞運會規模最大的建設項目是什麼？

sentences.english: Move to the corner of 15th St. & 10th Ave.
sentences.chinese: 移動到第15屆聖夫角落與第10位。

sentences.english: Aramark has provided catering services at 13 previous Olympic Games.
sentences.chinese: 愛瑪客曾爲13屆奧運會提供過服務。

sentences.english: This film won Golden Bear at the 57th Berlin International Film Festival in 2007.
sentences.chinese: 本片獲第57屆柏林電影節最佳影片金熊獎。

sentences.english: Object. Should stop immediately use the name of the 28th CSSA.
sentences.chinese: 反對，應該立即停止以28屆名義開展活動。

sentences.english: The 106th Canton Fair Phase II is in progress.
sentences.chinese: 第106屆廣交會二期正在進行中。

sentences.english: The 14th National Cancer Prevention Week begins tomorrow.
sentences.chinese: 第14屆全國腫瘤防治宣傳週活動即將啓動。

sentences.english: The 29th Olympic Summer Games will be held in our country in 2008.
sentences.chinese: 第29屆夏季奧運會將於2008年在我國舉行。

sentences.english: The 17th World Cup was held in two Asian countries.
sentences.chinese: 第17屆世界盃是在兩個亞洲國家興辦的。

sentences.english: The 29th Olympics were successfully hosted in Beijing and Chinese athletes won the most gold medals.
sentences.chinese: 第29屆奧運會在北京成功舉辦，中國金牌數第一。

sentences.english: India will celebrate its 57th Republic day on January 26.
sentences.chinese: 印度將在26日慶祝第57屆的共和日。

sentences.english: This 115th session is scheduled to conclude on 25 January.
sentences.chinese: 本次第115屆會議預定於1月25日結束。

sentences.english: This marked the beginning of the 131st commencement.
sentences.chinese: 校歌響起，標誌着第131屆畢業典禮正式開始。

sentences.english: Skiing, ice-skating and ice hockey are among the 7 Winter Game sports.
sentences.chinese: 冬奧會舉辦了7屆，有滑雪，滑冰和冰上曲棍球。

sentences.english: The 82nd Annual Academy Awards will be presented on Sunday, March 7, and televised live on ABC beginning at 5 p.m. PT/ 8 p.m. ET.
sentences.chinese: 第82屆年度學院獎將在三月七日，週日舉行。

definition: auxiliary verb introducing future action: may (be able to)/will (cause)/should (enable)/going to
to fight for/to strive for/to win over
large place used for a specific purpose/stage/scene (of a play)/classifier for sporting or recreational activities/classifier for number of exams
threshing floor/classifier for events and happenings: spell, episode, bout
to compete/to take part in a competition
back of neck/item/thing/term (in a mathematical formula)/sum (of money)/classifier for principles, items, clauses, tasks, research projects etc
